1. Nadam se da će naš tim *pobijediti* na sutrašnjoj utakmici. (I hope that our team will *win* tomorrow's game.)
2. Oni su uspeli *pobediti* bolest zahvaljujući savremenoj medicini. (They managed to *overcome* the illness thanks to modern medicine.)
3. Kada su se oženili, osećaj da je *pobedio* u životu bio je neprocenjiv za njega. (When they got married, the feeling that he had *won* in life was priceless for him.)
4. Ako želiš da *pobediš* na ispitu, moraš da učiš svaki dan. (If you want to *succeed* on the exam, you have to study every day.)
5. Uvek je u pravu, nikada ne dozvoljava da ga neko *pobedi*. (He is always right, he never allows anyone to *defeat* him.)
6. Na kraju je uspeo da *pobedi* svoje strahove i krene napred. (In the end, he managed to *conquer* his fears and move forward.)
7. Prošli put si *pobedio*, ali ovaj put će biti drugačije. (Last time you *won*, but this time it will be different.)
8. Njihova ideja je *pobedila* na takmičenju za najbolji startap. (Their idea *won* at the competition for the best startup.)
9. Već dugo se borim da *pobedim* svoju lenjost. (I have been struggling to *overcome* my laziness for a long time.)
10. Bio je uveren da će *pobediti* u debati, ali se na kraju ispostavilo da je grešio. (He was convinced that he would *win* in the debate, but it turned out in the end that he was wrong.)